{
  "texts": [
    " Metaphors use well-known English sayings or phrases and turn them into a question.",
    "It requires recognition of the saying that is presented in a slightly different form and an understanding of the metaphoric meaning Example: What kind of coals do you need to take coals to Newcastle?",
    " Math word puzzles are known to cause problems for LLMs.",
    "We therefore only include a few of them and also combine them with questions that look mathematical but need no calculation for a correct answer.",
    "Example: If Susan is running faster than Joe, but slower than Mike and the three do a 100 meter race, who will win?"
  ]
}